{
  "stem": "2581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I really don't remember much about my brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the hardest thing is I can't remember his face.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's no way to get a picture.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know the general outline of this face, the color of his hair.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I know he was-- I was the quiet boy and he was the lively one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But I cannot-- I'm trying so hard to try to remember his face, and I just can't.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, his name-- we used to call him Lolick.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was Loeser, probably the Hebrew name of Haleuser.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one thing that all the time that keeps coming back to me [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that he must have looked up to me, because wherever I went, he was there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And if there can be a humorous side, the  funny thing was one day he saw me talking to us schoolmate, to a girl.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he came running home to his-- to my parents saying, you must hear this, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He must-- this is Faftya.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Faftya went on a date.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I saw him with  a girl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But he would always find something to bring to the parents about me, but not-- not in a complaining sense, but being proud of-- of his brother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And shortly before they deported us from our hometown, our father made for us suits from fabric that is usually made for grown up people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this is what he had, and this is what he made.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we wore it practically most of the time because we were expecting to being deported from our town, because we saw trucks-- trucks with people from the vicinity passing our town on the way to Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't know where they were going.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
